de.mrapp.android.preference

Class ResolutionPreference

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.preference.Preference
      • de.mrapp.android.preference.AbstractDialogPreference
        • de.mrapp.android.preference.AbstractValidateableDialogPreference<java.lang.CharSequence>
          • de.mrapp.android.preference.ResolutionPreference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.DialogInterface.OnClickListener, android.content.DialogInterface.OnDismissListener, de.mrapp.android.dialog.MaterialDialogBuilder.Validator, de.mrapp.android.validation.Validateable<java.lang.CharSequence>, java.lang.Comparable<android.preference.Preference>

    public class ResolutionPreference
extends AbstractValidateableDialogPreference<java.lang.CharSequence>
    A preference, which allows to enter a two-dimensional image or video resulution via two EditText widgets. The entered resolution will only be persisted, if confirmed by the user.
    Since:
    1.3.0
    Author:
    Michael Rapp

        Parameters:
        context - The context, which should be used by the preference, as an instance of the class Context
        attributeSet - The attributes of the XML tag that is inflating the preference, as an instance of the type AttributeSet
        defaultStyle - The default style to apply to this preference. If 0, no style will be applied (beyond what is included in the theme). This may either be an attribute resource, whose value will be retrieved from the current theme, or an explicit style resource
        defaultStyleResource - A resource identifier of a style resource that supplies default values for the preference, used only if the default style is 0 or can not be found in the theme. Can be 0 to not look for defaults
